From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 13:51:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== mark core-only using fields as private ====

mm/damon/core: hide struct fields from callers

DAMON started with quite a few parameters.  It was simple and it wanted
to be flexible for future extensions.  Hence the core layer was focusing
on being simple rather than providing some protections for callers.
Instead, the callers were encouraged to directly manipulate internal
fieldss of the core structs.

Indeed it was helpful for DAMON's fast growth.  Nowadays, however, DAMON
has quite a number of parameters and complexities.  It also has four
core API callers that aimed for real world usage.  There are three more
sample callers.  Controlling them all with the open-coded way becomes
challenging.  One frequent challenge is control of direct reads/writes
of core struct fields from the callers.  It is especially challenging
because nearly all core struct fields are kernel-doc documented.  It
only enourages callers to directly reads/writes those.

Mark most core struct fields that not obviously to be directly accessed
from callers as private, to discourage direct access to those fields.

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
